@node "Introduction" "Introduction to Karami"
Sometimes ago, at TV, there was a show with Arthur with Karaoke (in France). It was really nice, and the idea was born: why couldn't I do the same thing with my favorite computer. Moreover I have bought a CDROM drive. So with Karami, you will be able to make Karaoke, of all your favorite songs on CD audios, tapes, etc...
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
To use Karami, you must have:
   - an Amiga (for sure) (very uncommon!)
   - a Kickstart 2.0 or higher
   - 1 Mb of RAM should be enough
   - a SCSI/Atapi CD-ROM drive (optionnal)
   - the soft @{"SkandalfoCDP" link "Recognising_CDDA" 0} (optionnal)

Karami has been sucessfully tested on 
   - an Amiga 1200 / 68020-28mhz / 6 Mb / Atapi CD-ROM
   - an Amiga 1200 / 68030-50mhz / 32 Mb / Pixel64 / Atapi CD-ROM
If you discover some bugs, please report me them.

Why 2 versions ?
The normal use Interrupts to abort playing immediately.
If that feature doesn't work on your machine, try the limited version !
@endnode

@node "Quick Tutorial" "Quick Tutorial"
@{b}* Lyrics of the song:@{ub}
You can import the lyrics from an ASCII text, done with one of your favorite text editor, or editing each line in the little window called 'Edit': you will have to use the menu Edit/AddLine to create a blank line to edit.
I think the better method is the fist one!

@{b}* Settings of the track audio of your CD-ROM:@{ub} (optionnal)
If you have a CD-ROM connected to your computer, Karami will drive it to play the track selected, during the displaying of the lyrics. If not ever done, you should give the name of the device and the unit of your drive, with the menu Prefs/Options. Don't forget to save the prefs, if you do not want to make that next time! You will have to give the number of the audio track to play with the menu Audio/source with setting Source as CD-ROM and selecting a number for the track. It's all.
You can test it is working with the menu Audio/play.

@{b}* Giving the times between each lyric:@{ub}
Press the button 'Record' in the window 'Control'. (If you have a CD-ROM, the song will start. If not, unpause your tape/CD/disc drive!) Now, you just have to click in the window 'Edit' to jump to the next lyric, when it is the moment. You must be as precise as possible.
Type ESC to abort a record.
You should click just a little in advance, so that later you can sing easily... (seeing before singing!)

@{b}* Controling your work:@{ub}
Press the button 'Play' in the window 'Control'. If some lyrics have been displayed earlier or later, you can adjust the time of each one in the window 'Time' with the arrows or by entering directly a value for the seconds and the mili-seconds.
You can abort the playing mode by pressing @{"'ESC'" link "Keyboard" 0} on your keyboard.
Repeat this work, until it is perfect!

@{b}* Beautifull extras:@{ub}
When you close the window 'Edit', you will have the screen of the final display, in which you can set your favorite font, put a nice picture in the background and select a colour for the lyrics.

@{b}* Saving your nice job:@{ub}
All is done, you're really happy: do not wait for a lack of electricity, I think you could become really unpleasant, so use the menu Project/SaveAs to save your work immediately.
@endnode

