@node "Windows" "Descriptions of windows"
@{b}* 'Project' window.@{ub}
In this window you can view all the lyrics of your song. Clicking on one will select it. At the start, you have just one lyric initialised, you must use the menu Edit/NewLine to have another one.
You can use the arrows top-bottom to select another lyric in the listview, even in the display screen.

@{b}* 'Edit' window.@{ub}
In this window you can edit the lyric selected in the project window. It is recommended to edit your song in a nice editor like CygnusED, and to import your ASCII text, the Editor in Karami, should just be used for modifications.
When you are recording a song, clicking in the window, will jump to the next lyric.
If you close the window, you will have the final display in its own screen.

@{b}* 'Control' window.@{ub}
In this window, you have the following buttons: 
@{u}'Play'@{uu} will start the selected song on your CD-ROM and display the lyrics synchronised with the song. Press @{"'ESC' on your keyboard to abort" link "Keyboard" 0}.
@{u}'PartPlay'@{uu} will start the song from the line selected in the listview. Very usefull when you want to adjust a time at the end of the song (to not listen all the song at each time!)
@{u}'Record'@{uu} will start the recording of all the differents times of apparitions of each lyric.
@{u}'Stop'@{uu} will stop a Playing or a Recording mode.
@{u}'PlayFinal'@{uu} the same as 'Play' but will open the screen display without ugly title bar, and is essential for graphic card owners (as they can not have 2 screens visible at the same time)
@{u}'Party'@{uu} is a mode to enjoy yourselves and yours friends in singing all the nice songs you have prepared. When you've got the black screen, insert a CD with the song to play, type the number of the track followed by enter and enjoy! When finished, type another track, or type ESC to exit.
You can abort a playing with @{"ESC" link "Keyboard" 0}.
Karami will search for the files in the drawer Lyrics/ or the drawer Lyrics/Author/ , so you can arrange your files by author to avoid to have a lot of files in the same drawer.
Your CDs must have been defined with @{"SkandalfoCDP" link "Recognising_CDDA" 0}.

@{b}* 'Time' window@{ub}
In this window, you will be able to adjust a time for the selected lyric.

@{b}* The display screen@{ub}
Here you have what you will see a the end...
Press ESC to switch back to the little editor.
You can now use the menu 'Display' to modify the justification,the screen mode, the font,the palette or put a nice picture in background: just look at the @{"description of the menus" link "Menus" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Menus" "Description of menus"
@{b}* Project@{ub}
   @{u}** New@{uu}
      This will initialise a new project with one lyric. All your work will
      be lost, if not saved! A requester will ask your confirmation.
   @{u}** Load@{uu}
      To load an old project you have ever done.
   @{u}** Save@{uu}
      To save the current project, without rehaving the requester.
   @{u}** Save As@{uu}
      To give a name to your project, to save it.
   @{u}** Import ASCII/SkandalfoCDP@{uu}
      To load an ascii file or a LYric file for SkandalfoCDP as lyrics for
      your song.
   @{u}** Export ASCII/SkandalfoCDP@{uu}
      To save an ascii file or a LYric file for SkandalfoCDP of your work. 
   @{u}** About@{uu}
      Do not forget the author, please.
   @{u}** Quit@{uu}
      Are you sure?

@{b}*Edit@{ub}
   @{u}** Cut@{uu}
      Delete the selected lyric and copy it to the buffer.
   @{u}** Copy@{uu}
      Copy the selected lyric to the buffer.
   @{u}** Paste@{uu}
      Copy the buffer to the selected lyric.
   @{u}** Insert line@{uu}
      Insert a new initialiser lyric in the list.
   @{u}** Add line@{uu}
      Insert a new initialised lyric in the list, just after the current
      lyric.
   @{u}** Insert author&title@{uu}
      Insert a new lyric with tha name of the author and the title of the
      song if the CD in the @{"CD-ROM has been recognised" link "Recognising_CDDA" 0}.

@{b}*Audio@{ub}
   @{u}**Source@{uu}
     Open a window in which you will set if you use the CD-ROM or not for
     your song in the gadget Source (External / CD-ROM / HardDisk file).
     You will also set the track to play in the gadget Track with the number
     (and the name of the song, if @{"your CD has been recognized" link "Recognising_CDDA" 0}).
     In the case of a HardDisk sample, you must choose it with a requester on
     your hard disk.
   @{u}**Play@{uu}
     Start the CD-ROM with the track selected.
   @{u}**Stop@{uu}
     Stop the CD-ROM
   @{u}**Pause@{uu} (the shortcut is space)
     Pause/Unpause the playing of the CD-ROM.
   @{u}**Backward@{uu}
     Jump 10 seconds backward in the playing.
   @{u}**Forward@{uu}
     Jump 10 seconds forward in the playing.

@{b}*Display@{ub} (available also on the display screen)
   @{u}**Left@{uu}
     Alter the justification of the selected lyric to the left in the
     display (not the Editor).
   @{u}**Middle@{uu}
     Centre the selected lyric.
   @{u}**Right@{uu}
     Set to the right the selected lyric.
   @{u}**ScreenMode@{uu}
     Select a screen mode  for the display screen.
   @{u}**ScreenFont@{uu}
     Select a font to display the lyric.
   @{u}**Palette@{uu}
     Select the palette for the background and the lyrics.
   @{u}**Picture@{uu}
     Select a picture for the background of the screen.
   @{u}**Color@{uu}
     Select a color to display the lyric when you've got a picture.
   @{u}**Del.Picture@{uu}
     Free the picture from the memory and the screen (of course)

@{b}*Prefs@{ub}
   @{u}**ScreenMode@{uu}
     Select a screen mode for the screen of Karami.
   @{u}**ScreenFont@{uu}
     Select a font for the screen of Karami.
   @{u}**Palette@{uu}
     Alter the palette of the screen.
   @{u}**Options@{uu}
     Allows you to set the device and the unit of your CD-ROM drive. You can
     set the path @{"to recognise your CDs audio" link "Recognising_CDDA" 0}.
     You can set the value of ms for the buttons +/-.
     You can select your external player for playing hard disk samples.
   @{u}**SavePrefs@{uu}
     Save the prefs definitively.
@endnode

@node "Keyboard" "Some keys to use"

Use the ESC key, to abort a playing or a recording of a song. 
@{u}Warning:@{uu} @{b}@{bg shine}You CAN NOT ABORT between each time, so press ESC and just wait...@{ub}@{bg back}
NEW : Since v1.2, with interrupts, abort is done immediately ! (you must use the normal version for this feature.)

Use the arrows keys, to select a lyric in the listview of the project window.

Use the +/- keys, to alter the spacing between the lines when you'are on the display screen.
@endnode

@node "Recognising_CDDA" "Recognising your CD audios"
To recognise your CDs, Karami uses the IDs files created with the excellent soft SkandalfoCDP by Juan J. García de Soria. You will have to set the path of this files in the options of the preferences. Now when a CD is recognised, when selecting a track, you will have the name of the song, and when saving a project, it will propose it also.

SkandalfoCDP can be found on Aminet in disk/cdrom/
@endnode

@node "History" "History of Karami"


   @{bg shine}V1.0 / September 1996@{bg back}
          ¤ First public release


   @{bg shine}V1.1 / November 1996@{bg back}  
          ¤ Screens are now opened with Tags (instead of an old way
            like in KS1.3 ...) So you can now use overscan screens
            and it's okay! (So Yann, happy?)
          ¤ GadTools menus
          ¤ In Edit menu, now a new item 'Add Line' for convenience
          ¤ Bug of 'Cut' on Last Item removed (now flashing... instead
            of exiting the prog!)
          ¤ Busy pointer everywhere on windows when needed
          ¤ Entierely localised !!! (french catalog included)
          ¤ And some little things...


   @{bg shine}V1.2 / February 1998 @{bg back}  
          ¤ New audio-source : a sample on hard-disk played with one of
            your favorite players. (idea by Didier Lorthios)
          ¤ Export/Import with LYrics of SkandalfoCDPlayer
          ¤ Export ASCII
          ¤ Enforcer hit sometimes when selecting a screen mode removed
          ¤ Keyboard interrupts to abort playing immediately (perhaps
            it doesn't work on some machines... you've a second version
            of Karami without interrupts. Try yourself. It works perfectly
            on my computer!)


   @{bg shine}V1.3 / August 1998 @{bg back}  
          ¤ Major fix for graphic card users.
            As graphics cards do not allow to drag the screens with their
            title bar and do not allow to see 2 screens at the same time
            now you've got :
              - a menu in the screen 'final display screen'
              - a new button 'playfinal' to launch the play on the screen
              - the background picture was crashing the Amiga...
          ¤ When failed to open the screen, open a screen mode requester
            to give a new screen mode instead of crashing!
          ¤ Now allow to join 2 lines in the little editor (but remember
            use CygnusEd instead for typing all the lyrics!!!)
          ¤ Remember the last font in the font requester instead of always
            giving topaz/8 (thanks to Ott M Aaloe & Curt Esser for the
            example on that feature)

@endnode

@node "Shareware" "Shareware request"
